reviews.text: Wonderful app, I've been trying many different image editing apps recently, and I really like the filters and effects that this app has. It also has wide range of editing options which makes the editing process entertaining , easy and quick. I would definitely recommend this to whomever looking for a qualified and efficient image editing app. Thanks to the designer for the user friendly interface, the programmer for doing such a good job and publishers.
reviews.replyText: Thank you for loving our product! We'll keep working on it! If you have any suggestions, please feel free to reach out. Have a good day ‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.text: When I first opened DoFoto I thought, generic AI editing clone.... I load an image and start applying filters, yawn... Then with one click, I was able to switch to only the background. AMAZING. EFFORTLESS. Without masking anything! I applied an AI ring in the wrong position and DoFoto is the ONLY app ive seen that allows you to reposition an AI filter intuitively. That is the GOLD STANDARD now that other apps must live up to. Awesome job truely a game changer. Keep up the good work!
reviews.replyText: Welcome to DoFoto! üíïThank you for your love and encouragement. We will keep working on it!üíï

reviews.text: A ton of options on the free version and it only gets better with pro. I only saw one ad while editing for almost an hour so I was able to get much more done by comparison to other apps like this. Options for multiple subjects not just the person or object in the front and I love the variety of retouches for the face. I highly recommend anyone getting this app for all of their basic editing needs and more.
reviews.replyText: We are so glad to know that you like our product, if you have any suggestions, feel free to contact us. Have a good dayü•∞

reviews.text: I put some of my pictures in free mode, and the program still has snap. Can't align my pictures properly when I'm doing an overlay. There's an auto adjust that puts the pictures in line and that defeats the purpose of free mode period other than that this program is really great

Liked the app so much that I purchased "lifetime pro." I hope the app developers continue to develop and improve on the current app features, e.g. be able to add custom backgrounds to ai cutouts from photos on my phone, bring photos to life (movement), easier to combine characters from different photos, placing them in front or behind each other, then replacing the background (in fewer steps, without having to save and then reload photo edit after each step). Recommended, can get even better.
reviews.replyText: Thank you so much for your support! We truly value your feedback and are committed to continuously developing and enhancing the app. Your suggestions of streamlining the photo editing process will be considered in our future updates.Thanks again for your recommendation and for being a valued part of our community!

reviews.text: Being a photographer by profession I can honestly say this is one of the very best AI photo editors out there! The tools in this editor really stand out from all the rest! So much so that I paid for the premium within 5 minutes of downloading & opening the app! The only beef I have is that the removal tool is a bit laggy & slow, but that's so minute compared to how amazing all the rest of the tools are! Full 5 stars!
reviews.replyText: Hello Megan, thank you very much for using our DoFoto. We deeply respect your feedback about removal tool. We will try to combine your feedback with our R&D, in order to provide better products. ‚ù§Ô∏èü§ùüòò Best regards.

reviews.text: Does the trick for sure, plus the subscription option is very nice being that it offers a one-time deal, which is always a major plus in my book as I dread having to manage payments when money hardly stretches far at all these days(Thanks Federal Reserveü§¨). MANY different little doodaderies included and things you can do to edit photos with this app. Easily the best I've come across so far, short of photoshop-tier editing, all things considered!

I am picky with photo apps. It comes to, how many of needed features? How do these features work? What are the purchase? How is the save process. This is a typical photo editing app. I have not found the magic do everything app yet and still have to go through 4 apps with art stuff. The features present work very well. Very affordable for what you get at 8$/year, no lifetime options though. The app keep file quality it does not keep the original file name. 4-stars worth the buy.

app.AIReview:
Photo Editor: Retouch, Enhance ‚Äì A Detailed Review

Overview

Photo Editor: Retouch, Enhance, developed by DoFoto, presents itself as a comprehensive free face photo editing app aimed at users seeking quick and easy enhancements to their portraits. With over 9.4 million installs and a robust 4.79 rating from nearly 72,000 users, the app has clearly established itself within the crowded photography editing landscape. The core promise ‚Äì ‚Äústunning photos with unlimited creativity!‚Äù ‚Äì is supported by a suite of features including an AI Retouch & Face Editor, an AI Photo Enhancer, aesthetic filters, and even a Pic Collage Maker. This review will delve into these features to assess whether DoFoto truly delivers on its ambitious claims.

Key Features

The app‚Äôs feature set is intentionally broad, reflecting the ‚Äúall-in-one‚Äù marketing approach. Here's a breakdown of the key elements:

  • AI Retouch & Face Editor: This is arguably the centerpiece of the app. It allows users to manipulate facial features with surprising precision. Adjustments include smoothing skin, reshaping the jawline, altering eye size and shape, and even adjusting nose dimensions. The AI component purportedly assists in making these adjustments feel more natural than traditional sliders would.
  • AI Photo Enhancer: This feature utilizes artificial intelligence to automatically improve photo quality ‚Äì boosting brightness, contrast, sharpness, and color saturation. It‚Äôs designed for quickly elevating low-resolution or poorly lit images.
  • Aesthetic Filters & AI Effects: A selection of pre-designed filters are available, categorized by style (e.g., vintage, black and white, artistic). The ‚ÄúAI effects‚Äù are a newer addition that supposedly leverages AI to add dynamic overlays and enhancements beyond traditional filters. Examples include adding bokeh or simulated light leaks.
  • Perfect Body Editor: This feature is specifically designed for altering body shapes ‚Äì primarily targeting the waist, hips, and arms.
  • Face Retouch App: A dedicated tool focused solely on refining facial features.
  • Pic Collage Maker: Allows users to create collages by combining multiple photos with various layouts and stickers.

Strengths

  • Ease of Use: The app‚Äôs interface is remarkably intuitive. The layout is clean, and the controls are logically arranged, making it accessible even for novice photo editors. Navigating between features is straightforward.
  • Effective AI Retouching (Initially): The AI-powered face editor demonstrates considerable potential in quickly smoothing skin and making subtle adjustments to facial features. The results can be impressive with minimal effort ‚Äì especially for users new to advanced editing techniques.
  • Photo Enhancement Capabilities: The AI Photo Enhancer is genuinely effective at improving the overall quality of photos, particularly those with poor lighting or low resolution. It‚Äôs a convenient tool for quickly boosting images before sharing them online.
  • High Install Numbers & Positive Rating: The immense popularity (9.4 million installs) and high rating (4.79/5) suggest that the app addresses a significant user need, and many users find it valuable.

Areas for Improvement

  • AI Over-Reliance: While the AI tools are effective, they can sometimes produce overly smoothed or unnatural results if not used carefully. Users should be mindful of this and manually adjust settings as needed to avoid an artificial look.
  • Filter Variety & Quality: While there‚Äôs a decent selection of filters, some feel generic and lack distinct character. The quality of the AI effects is inconsistent; some are impressive, while others appear somewhat gimmicky.
  • Limited Manual Control: Compared to more sophisticated photo editing apps, DoFoto offers limited manual control over key parameters like shadows, highlights, and curves. This can be frustrating for users who prefer a hands-on approach.
  • ‚ÄúPerfect Body Editor‚Äù ‚Äì Potential for Misuse: The ‚ÄúPerfect Body Editor‚Äù is arguably the most problematic feature, given the potential for promoting unrealistic beauty standards. Clearer disclaimers regarding its use are needed.

User Experience

The user experience is generally smooth and responsive. Image loading times are reasonable, and transitions between features are seamless. The app‚Äôs performance remains stable even when applying multiple filters or effects simultaneously. The touch controls are well-optimized, providing accurate and predictable responses. However, the abundance of options can occasionally feel overwhelming to new users. A guided tutorial would greatly improve onboarding.

Value for Money

As a free app with no in-app purchases (that I could find during testing), DoFoto offers excellent value for money. The core features ‚Äì including the AI Retouch & Face Editor, Photo Enhancer, and filter collection ‚Äì are fully accessible without any restrictions. This makes it an attractive option for anyone looking to easily enhance their photos on a budget.

Conclusion

Photo Editor: Retouch, Enhance is a surprisingly capable free photo editing app that delivers impressive results thanks to its AI-powered tools. While the app isn't perfect‚Äîparticularly concerning filter variety and some potential issues with the AI ‚Äì it‚Äôs an excellent choice for users seeking a simple, intuitive way to enhance their photos quickly and effectively. The high install numbers and positive rating are well-deserved, indicating that DoFoto has successfully met the needs of a large audience. It's a solid entry point into photo editing for beginners and a convenient tool for casual photographers who want to make quick improvements on the go. I would rate it 4 out of 5 stars.
